The paper discusses the development of cortical learning algorithms based on the Hierarchical Temporal Memory (HTM) for use in intelligent agents for mining real-time databases. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of intelligent agents implies that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the mention of real-time datasets suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
